Class FragmentExtractor

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.dev.jjs.impl.FragmentExtractor

public class FragmentExtractor
extends java.lang.Object

A class that extracts a fragment of code based on a supplied liveness condition.

Method Detail

methodFor

public static JMethod methodFor(JsStatement stat,
                                JavaToJavaScriptMap map)
Return the Java method corresponding to stat, or null if there isn't one. It recognizes JavaScript of the form function foo(...) { ...}, where foo is the name of the JavaScript translation of a Java method.

createOnLoadedCall

public java.util.List<JsStatement> createOnLoadedCall(int splitPoint)
Create a call to AsyncFragmentLoader#onLoad.

extractStatements

public java.util.List<JsStatement> extractStatements(FragmentExtractor.LivenessPredicate livenessPredicate,
                                                     FragmentExtractor.LivenessPredicate alreadyLoadedPredicate)
Assume that all code described by alreadyLoadedPredicate has been downloaded. Extract enough JavaScript statements that the code described by livenessPredicate can also run. The caller should ensure that livenessPredicate includes strictly more live code than alreadyLoadedPredicate.

findAllMethodsInJavaScript

public java.util.Set<JMethod> findAllMethodsInJavaScript()
Find all Java methods that still exist in the resulting JavaScript, even after JavaScript inlining and pruning.
